    <description>Basileus is a an introductory level tactical medieval wargame. This is the fifth module of the &amp;quot;A la Charge!&amp;quot; series.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each turn is composed of 6 phases:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Movement of Player 1&amp;#10;    Combat of Player 1&amp;#10;    Movement of Player 2&amp;#10;    Combat of Player 2&amp;#10;    Check victory conditions&amp;#10;    Advance the Turn Marker&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Five battles are included:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Arcadiopolis, 970 (Byzantines vs. Rus/Bulgars/Pechenegs)&amp;#10;    Dorostolon 1, 971 (Byzantines vs. Rus/Pechenegs)&amp;#10;    Dorostolon 2, 971 (Byzantines vs. Rus)&amp;#10;    Dorostolon 3, 971 (Byzantines vs. Rus)&amp;#10;    Beroia, 1122(Byzantines vs. Pechenegs)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Many wargame concepts are introduced like Zone of Control, moving from hexagon to hexagon, command, firing long distance or close combat (melee), checking morale and retreating.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A battle lasts between 30-60 mins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
